deletePtnCut(25.10)                                        deletePtnCut(25.10)

Name
       deletePtnCut - Deletes all the partition cuts

Syntax
       deletePtnCut

       [-help]

       {-ptn {<ptnName> | <ptnNameList>} | -all}

       Deletes all the partition cuts.

Parameters
       -all   Deletes all the partition cuts.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each deletePtnCut parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deletePtnCut

       -ptn {<ptnName> | <ptnNameList>}
              Specifies the name of the partition, or the list  of  partitions
              for which partition cuts are deleted.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The following command deletes partition cuts for partition sheet17:

       deletePtnCut -ptn sheet17

